The late gospel star&#8217;s family says a memorial service will be held to remember the singer at the Grace Bible Church. JOHANNESBURG - Sfiso Ncwane's family says a memorial service will be held to remember the gospel star at the Grace Bible Church in Soweto on Friday. The award winning singer died on Monday at the Fourways Life Hospital after suffering from kidney failure. He'll be laid to rest in Durban on Saturday. Family spokesperson Sipho Makhabane says: A memorial service will be held at the Grace Bible Church in Soweto on Friday. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)